\par\par \b \uc2  Government has no special plans to boost rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 737 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie said here on Friday that neither the government nor \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would take any special measures to shore up the ailing rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Kwik said that the current weakness was only temporary and he believed the rupiah would strengthen once political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  subsided either before or after the upcoming August special session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body. \par \par \uc2  "The government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will not take (special) action because all of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators are satisfactory. If we take action, it will only cause the market to think that there's something serious going on," he told a media briefing following a meeting with Finance Minister Bambang Sudibyo and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  senior officials. \par \par \uc2  Kwik also held a meeting with several players in the currency markets earlier in the day. \par \par \uc2  "We're convinced that the current weakness in the rupiah is only temporary. That's why we won't take any action. We won't intervene or change the exchange rate system," he said. \par \par \uc2  The government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials have repeatedly said that the weakening in the currency had been largely due to non-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors as key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators have largely improved. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under strong pressure lately due to domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the run up to the MPR's forthcoming session. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid is scheduled to deliver a statement of accountability for his one year administration at the MPR's annual meeting. The country's political temperature has heated up in the approach to the August meeting amid signs of a possible impeachment attempt against the President. But top legislators have said that no such attempt is in the offing. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed steady at Rp 9,305 against the U.S. dollar on Thursday, almost unchanged from the previous day's close of Rp 9,310. \par \par \uc2  Currency traders said that the Indonesian currency fell to a range of between Rp 9,320 and Rp 9,350 in midday trading before recovering to Rp 9,305 in late trading. \par \par \uc2  The current exchange rate level is much lower than the government target for this year of Rp 7,000 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  Dealers attributed the late increase in the rupiah to intervention by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which they said, sold about $20 million in the afternoon session through state banks in a bid to shore up the ailing currency. \par \par \uc2  Kwik was also convinced that the rupiah would not drop to below Rp 10,000 because market players are now more confident about the outcome of August's assembly session. \par \par \uc2  "I doubt if the rupiah will fall to below the Rp 10,000 level (in the run up to August) because the market players now think that there's more certainty about the outcome of the assembly session," he said. \par \par \uc2  Kwik also said that the current weakness in the rupiah had so far not had a serious impact on the country's manufacturing sector because firms had imported raw materials when the rupiah was still at around Rp 7,000 per dollar last seen in February. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Bambang said that the rupiah remained very sensitive to the political atmosphere as the currency markets were still not mature enough in coming to terms with the changes taking place during the country's political transition to a democratic nation. \par \par \uc2  Bambang said that the MPR general session should not be a worry as it was being held in accordance with the constitution. He also said that strong criticism of the President by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  should not give rise to jitters because this was a normal part of democracy. \par \par \uc2  Bambang was convinced that the currency markets would gradually adapt to the new situation, and that the rupiah would strengthen. \par \par \uc2  "We hope the rupiah will firm up soon ... because I'm sure there will be a satisfactory resolution (to the current political conflict)," he said. \par \par \uc2  Bambang added that if the rupiah continued to weaken, it would undoubtedly hamper the country's overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery efforts. \par \par \uc2  Experts have said that the weakening in the rupiah as well as the inevitable increase in domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would inflate the cost of the country's bank recapitalization program, and hamper the crucial process of corporate debt restructuring. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw78005hz\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
