\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah weakness hurting manufacturing - Kadin. \b0\par\par\uc2 587 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Chairman of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) Aburizal Bakrie said on Monday that if the rupiah continued to stay at about Rp 9,000 per U.S. dollar, the country's manufacturing sector would have to cut production in a bid to halt losses. \par \par \uc2  Aburizal said that the ideal exchange rate level for the manufacturing sector was about Rp 7,000 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  He explained that a weak rupiah would result in higher costs of imported raw materials, which could not be automatically transferred to local customers as purchasing power had been reduced by the more than two-year \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  "The drop in the rupiah to about Rp 9,000 is really hurting the business sector," he said. \par \par \uc2  Aburizal was speaking to reporters at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . He was scheduled to meet with House Commission IX for the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and banking, but the hearing was delayed as only a number of the commission members showed up. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been badly hit recently, particularly due to domestic security and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of a key August General Session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body. \par \par \uc2  Many fear that the House and MPR members will use the annual meeting to impeach the President, who has in recent months been engaged in a tug of a war with the legislators. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended stronger at Rp 9,315 per U.S. dollar late on Monday, compared to Rp 9,320 on Friday. This is much lower than the government's Rp 7,000 target for this year. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie said late last week that the government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not take any special action to prop up the rupiah because the current weakness was only temporary and due to "noneconomic factors". \par \par \uc2  "If we take action, it will only cause the market to think that there's something serious going on," he said. \par \par \uc2  Kwik was confident that the rupiah would be stronger once current political problems had been resolved, as the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals had improved. \par \par \uc2  Aburizal also urged the House to immediately take measures to ensure legal certainty for investors to do business in the country. \par \par \uc2  He said that the illegal seizure of company assets, including land, by the people could prompt investors to withdraw from the country. \par \par \uc2  "There has to be an industrial peace," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that legal certainty and the security condition were crucial to reviving business confidence in the country and to help strengthen the local currency. \par \par \uc2  Aburizal was optimistic that if domestic social and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  subsided, the rupiah would strengthen again. \par \par \uc2  He said that the country's key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors were positive enough to support a stronger exchange rate of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  He expected the rupiah to strengthen after August's MPR session. \par \par \uc2  Elsewhere, Aburizal also said that the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) must press ahead with its asset disposal program to help revive investor confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "IBRA must speed up its asset sale program," he said, adding that the government should not be reluctant to sell at a discount. \par \par \uc2  He added that a resolution to the country's massive corporate sector overseas debt was crucial to rebuilding confidence. \par \par \uc2  He also said that the government's economics team must be well coordinated in taking \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures to revive confidence, particularly among foreign investors. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw7b0051a\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'Ekonomi will recover if LoI is implemented'. \b0\par\par\uc2 439 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 July 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  DEN Chairman Emil Salim is convinced that the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will recover if the letter of intent (LoI) \par \par \uc2  between the government and the IMF is implemented. \par \par \uc2  "In 2001-2002 the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will go back to normal again just like before 1997 if the letter of intent is implemented. After that we \par \par \uc2  start the development stage," he said in a hearing between the National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Council (DEN) and the National \par \par \uc2  Businessmen Development Council (DPUN) with the House of Representative yesterday. \par \par \uc2  According to Senior \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Minister Kwik Kian Gie's letter to IMF Deputy Director Stanley Fisher, the government has yet to \par \par \uc2  finish 16 more items before the final draft of the second LoI under the leadership of Abdurrahman Wahid is signed in August. \par \par \uc2  The unfinished sectors include among others IBRA's responsibility, Bank Rakyat Indonesia recapitalization, and establishment of \par \par \uc2  a committee that will handle troubled debtors. \par \par \uc2  Positive indication \par \par \uc2  Emil Salim said he still believes with the prediction that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will reach 3%-4% growth this year. According to him, the \par \par \uc2  Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is no longer in the 'hole' like during the crisis in 1997-1998. The recovery process has already given positve \par \par \uc2  indications although not quite out of the hole yet. \par \par \uc2  The most important factor to come out of the prolonged crisis is to maintain security stability, he said. The DEN chairman also \par \par \uc2  lamented the rumors that spread in the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  which were then followed by violence as it would only hurt the stability. Such \par \par \uc2  condition, he added, is directly related to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process, mainly the foreign investors' trusts on the security \par \par \uc2  guarantee in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  As for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  aspect, Emil said the recovery effort is already on the right track. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah dived immediately over the Rp9,000 level after the bomb blasted at the Attorney General's Office and not because \par \par \uc2  of an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factor," he said. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political condition will dominantly affect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability, which is already starting to show recovery. Emil \par \par \uc2  also agreed that each political elites should restrain themselves from issuing statements that attack one another and instead they \par \par \uc2  should show optimism for the sake of recovery. \par \par \uc2  "Let's not only ask Gus Dur to fast [stop issuing statements]. Pak Amien [Rais, Chairman of the People's Consultative Assembly] or \par \par \uc2  Akbar [Tanjung, House Speaker] should also fast," he said. \par \par \uc2  Emil also touched on the legal enforcement. Very often the legal authorities or the government ignore the written law, and on \par \par \uc2  the contrary referred to individual statements. \par \par \uc2  He called on the House to fix the existing legal system instead of just criticizing them. (m12). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dw7c000e0\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
