\par\par \b \uc2  Government completes IMF reform target - Kwik. \b0\par\par\uc2 416 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie said on Tuesday that all reform targets agreed upon with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) had been finalized. \par \par \uc2  "We've already met the IMF's deadline," Kwik told reporters. \par \par \uc2  Kwik was commenting on an internal government deadline which falls this Thursday, to implement all reform programs as set out by the IMF. \par \par \uc2  Among the last reform tasks finalized by the government was the replacement of all directors of state-owned Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BRI), which was announced late Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  On Monday, the government spurred on to complete the recapitalization of Bank Bali in a bid to meet the reform's deadline. \par \par \uc2  The bank's recapitalization has been delayed due to a loan scandal last year that centered on the transfer of US$80 million under a questionable cessie agreement. \par \par \uc2  Other reform tasks include the recapitalization of BRI, Bank Negara Indonesia (BNI), as well as a 1999 audit of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  IMF chief representative for Indonesia John R. Dodsworth told news agency Dow Jones that the government should meet all reforms under its latest Letter of Intent (LoI) to the IMF within the "next few days". \par \par \uc2  The LoI contains the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program. Indonesia's compliance to the LoI is a prerequisite in obtaining the IMF's financial bailout. \par \par \uc2  However, a volatile political climate has made it difficult for the government to implement \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies with market sentiments reacting sensitively to any \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The rupiah took a steep dive against the U.S. dollar in late April, but had already been weakening since early this year largely due to political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The government is doing a good job of putting all of these things into place in difficult circumstances," Dodsworth said. \par \par \uc2  The completion of the reforms is vital in securing a third tranche of loans set for August, that may range between $380 million to $400 million. \par \par \uc2  The government failed to meet this year's first LoI deadline in April, prompting the IMF to delay the disbursement of the second tranche of loans of $400 million. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia obtained the funds after meeting the requirements of a second LoI in May and has thus far received $700 million from the IMF. \par \par \uc2  The loan is part of the IMF's $5 billion financial bailout package signed earlier this year to assist a three-year \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development program for Indonesia. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw7j005ss\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
