\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah books strong showing for second day. \b0\par\par\uc2 739 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah booked a strong showing for the second consecutive day on Wednesday ahead of President Abdurrahman Wahid's key appearance at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  today. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah broke through the 9,000 level against the U.S. dollar in morning trading amid reports of intervention by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  But the Indonesian currency retreated in afternoon trading due to corporate demand for American greenbacks. At the close of trading, the rupiah was quoted at Rp 9,018 per U.S. dollar compared to Rp 9,285 on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  The local currency has been under strong pressure over the past couple of weeks, plunging to a 21-month low of Rp 9,570 per dollar last week, due to domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said that investors, who had been in long U.S. dollar positions began taking profits on Tuesday after the rupiah failed to breakthrough the 9,570 level. \par \par \uc2  The change in market trend was incited by rumors that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had sold dollars through state banks to shore up the ailing rupiah. \par \par \uc2  But dealers said reports that the government has met the International Monetary Fund deadline for implementing key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs were the most rational reasons why many market players bought the Indonesian currency. \par \par \uc2  The slight rise in the interest rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory notes to 13.45 percent on Wednesday compared to 13.11 percent last week also contributed to the rupiah's strength. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman is scheduled to speak at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Thursday (today) to defend his recent dismissal of Laksamana Sukardi and Yusuf Kalla from his coalition Cabinet and the currency market clearly will be listening closely. \par \par \uc2  Laksamana is an executive of the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle, the largest political party, and Kalla is a member of Golkar, the giant political party in power for the last 30 years. \par \par \uc2  Some analysts have said that if Abdurrahman's explanations fail to satisfy angry and exasperated legislators, they might be sufficiently incensed to begin the process of unseating the President. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman is scheduled to meet with the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), the highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body, in August to give an account for his 10 months in power. \par \par \uc2  There have been fears that domestic political tensions will increase in the run up to the August session, even though several top politicians have assured that Abdurrahman would not be impeached at the session. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Finance Minister Bambang Sudibyo said on Wednesday that the strengthening of the rupiah was purely a result of market forces and not due to government intervention. \par \par \uc2  Bambang said that the President could not order \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to intervene because \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is now independent of the executive branch of government. \par \par \uc2  He expects the rupiah to further strengthen to the Rp 8,000 level, especially if Abdurrahman's appearance at the House goes well. \par \par \uc2  But he admitted that the local currency would remain volatile for the time being as the market is still adjusting to the country's new democratic political climate. \par \par \uc2  "The market will understand after a while, and the rupiah will strengthen again," Bambang said. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie dismissed speculation that the government was considering changing the current free floating foreign exchange system in a bid to strengthen the ailing rupiah. \par \par \uc2  He said that Indonesia had not enough forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  to impose a fixed exchange rate system, and even if it had, the government would need agreement from the IMF to take such a drastic step. \par \par \uc2  He said no such plan was discussed at the recent meeting with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  announced on Tuesday that the country's gross foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  fell to US$27.31 billion in the week ending last Friday, compared to $27.49 billion in the previous week. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah's rebound was felt regionally, providing a mild fillip for other Southeast Asian currencies. \par \par \uc2  In Singapore, the U.S. dollar fetched 44.52 Philippine pesos in late trading, down from 44.64 a day earlier. \par \par \uc2  The greenback was also weaker at 1.745 Singapore dollars from 1.747, 40.175 Thai baht from 40.295, 1,112.100 South Korean won from 1,112.135. But the international currency rose against the Taiwan dollar to 31.034 from 30.938.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw7k005u7\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
