st. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  NO BATTLEFIELDS PLEASE \par \par \uc2  Jakarta Military Commander Gen. Ryamizard Ryacudu has called on political \par \par \uc2  leaders not to mobilize their followers on the occasion of the general session \par \par \uc2  of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), due to take place in August. \par \par \uc2  This is a timely warning to political leaders to convey the message to their \par \par \uc2  supporters that they must keep their heads cool and not turn Jakarta into a \par \par \uc2  battle field. \par \par \uc2  Jakarta has become a hotbed of political conflict, and political debate now \par \par \uc2  dominates life in the capital city. \par \par \uc2  There are several issues which may see demonstrators take to the streets. \par \par \uc2  These include the Soeharto case and the religious violence in Ambon. Corruption \par \par \uc2  in high places can also equally excite an orgy of demonstrations. \par \par \uc2  Unsettling happening like these exert a major impact on life in this big \par \par \uc2  city. Depending on the size of the demonstrations, which fill the population of Jakarta with fear and worry, they are also quite likely to dislocate the flow of traffic. \par \par \uc2  Political leaders should heed to the appeal of Gen. Ryamizard because as Jakarta military commander he is responsible for security in the city and has an extremely heavy task in front of him to see that life functions normally despite the fact that members of parliament are debating hot political issues. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  UNDERSTANDING THE MEANING OF CRITICISM \par \par \uc2  Criticisms of President Abdurrahman Wahid are becoming louder. The latest \par \par \uc2  verbal attacks were made   amongst others by Akbar Tanjung,  Golkar Party \par \par \uc2  general chairman concurrently Speaker of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR), and \par \par \uc2  Nurcholis Madjid, one of the country's Moslem intellectuals. \par \par \uc2  Akbar raised objections to the controversial stances and policies \par \par \uc2  frequently shown by the president which had led to the creation of an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation. Madjid worried about the president's stances which had the potential of leading to scandals. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation may well cause the country to plunge into a second \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis that could be worse than the first one and even bring about total collapse. \par \par \uc2  Although  Akbar's criticisms were well intentioned, they drew strong \par \par \uc2  reactions from Wahid's supporters whose loyalty to him have hardened. \par \par \uc2  All of this has caused an escalation in  political controversy ahead of the \par \par \uc2  president's appearance at the DPR to answer the House's interpellation on July 20 and the annual session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) slated to be held in August. \par \par \uc2  We appeal to all of the nation's components not to misunderstand Akbar's statement and not to be provoked into misunderstanding his criticisms, because we are now living in a democratic situation which is quite different from that in the New Order era.-Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dw7k0056e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
