\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  to install bank inspectors next week. \b0\par\par\uc2 543 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will permanently install its supervisory officials in domestic banks starting early next week in a bid to improve the effectiveness of its banking supervisory function, a senior official of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Idris Kadir of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's banking supervisory division said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials were being assigned to identify and assess the potential risk of the banks, including foreign exchange and lending risks. \par \par \uc2  He said the on-site supervision would begin at the giant state Bank Mandiri and later at state Bank Rakyat Indonesia, Bank Tabungan Negara and Bank Negara Indonesia, and five recapitalized banks, including Bank Lippo, Bank Central Asia, Bank Niaga, Bank Internasional Indonesia and Bank Danamon. \par \par \uc2  He said two supervisory officials would be installed in each bank, with four in Bank Mandiri because of its size. \par \par \uc2  "At the first stage, the on-site supervision will only cover the nine banks, given their dominant role in the industry," he added. \par \par \uc2  Idris said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had yet to decide on whether the new measure would also cover foreign banks operating in the country. \par \par \uc2  He said the supervision was part of an agreement with the International Monetary Fund (IMF), which is providing the country with a multibillion dollar bailout package. \par \par \uc2  Idris said the on-site supervision was deemed more effective than off-site which focused only on the analysis of financial reports. \par \par \uc2  He said an off-site supervision system was not able to detect and anticipate the potential risk of banks and to formulate immediate corrective and proactive action. \par \par \uc2  He explained that under the on-site supervision system, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials installed in the banks must report their findings routinely to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the IMF. \par \par \uc2  He said the findings would be discussed first with the top management of the monitored banks before they were reported to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Idris said that if the findings were significant enough, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would immediately order the particular bank's management to take corrective measures. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's banking sector had been poorly managed in the past and was seen as one of the primary factors sending the country into its current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial crisis. \par \par \uc2  The government has been \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  the equivalent of billions of dollars to help finance the costly bank recapitalization program. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  must ensure that banks were operating prudently in order to avoid a similar crisis from reoccurring in the future, Idris said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  sent inspectors to foreign banks last week to ensure that they met banking regulations, notably the rules on minimum net open positions in foreign exchange deals. \par \par \uc2  The move was mostly seen by analysts as an effort by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to curb speculation on the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah plunged to a 21-month low of 9,570 per dollar two weeks ago amid domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the crucial General Session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) in which President Abdurrahman Wahid will deliver an accountability report on his first year in power. \par \par \uc2  Political tension has increased in the run-up to the August session of the MPR, the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body which can unseat the President. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw7r006nx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
