\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah won't drop during MPR session - Economist. \b0\par\par\uc2 685 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The rupiah is not likely to weaken much in the run up to the Aug. 7 through Aug. 18 People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) General Session as some have feared, according to an economist at a state bank. \par \par \uc2  Bank Mandiri chief economist Martin Panggabean said on Friday that the current weakening of the rupiah was only temporary as the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals had improved. \par \par \uc2  He also said that the move by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to curb speculation on the rupiah would also help limit the impact of political instability on the local currency. \par \par \uc2  "The pressure on the rupiah is only temporary ... and especially if \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  succeeds in curbing speculation in the rupiah by foreign banks," he said at a seminar on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended higher in late trading on Friday at 8,945 per U.S. dollar, compared to 8,970 on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been under strong pressure this month due to continuing political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the MPR session. \par \par \uc2  The local unit dropped to a 21-month low of Rp 9,570 per dollar earlier this month. \par \par \uc2  But sudden inspections by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials into bank dealing rooms to curb speculation has helped to prevent the rupiah from breaking through the Rp 10,000 level. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials said that it made the inspections to ensure that the banks abided by the existing prudential rulings, including a prohibition for banks from surpassing the 20 percent daily net open position limit, and from opening forward contracts worth more than US$5 million with nonresidents. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  acting governor Anwar Nasution also called on Singapore and other neighboring authorities on Thursday to help curb speculation on the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Many have feared that the rupiah could drop even lower than the Rp 10,000 level due to the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead and during the MPR session. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid will give an account of his first 10 months in power at the session, which is expected to be tense as many fear that the lawmakers will use the meeting to impeach the President. \par \par \uc2  The MPR is the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body and has the right to unseat the President. But several senior politicians have said that there would be no impeachment against the President in the August session. \par \par \uc2  Approximately 68,000 police and military troops will be on full alert during the 12-day session to maintain security, particularly in Jakarta and the surrounding areas. \par \par \uc2  He said that based on the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, the rupiah should be stronger. \par \par \uc2  Martin forecast that the rupiah would strengthen to about 8,500 per dollar this year, and to beyond 8,000 next year, driven particularly by the country's stronger export revenue. \par \par \uc2  He said that world trading volume would continue to increase over the next couple of years, and commodity prices would also rise. \par \par \uc2  Martin dismissed suggestions that the current weakening of the rupiah was similar to what happened in 1997 and 1998 when the rupiah dropped to as low as 17,000 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  He said that although the country's foreign debt level remained a problem now, as it was in 1997, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals had now improved, including in terms of the current account surplus and the relatively low inflation. \par \par \uc2  He also said that in 1997, the rupiah was overvalued, while now people believed that the rupiah was undervalued. \par \par \uc2  "The rupiah is now undervalued, there's no way to rise further from the current level," he said. \par \par \uc2  Martin, however, admitted that the rupiah would remain volatile over the near term due to the remaining political instability. \par \par \uc2  He also said that the country's current foreign exchange system was the most liberal in the world, even so than the system in Singapore. \par \par \uc2  He said that this was one factor causing the rupiah to be easily speculated upon by overseas players. \par \par \uc2  He said that introducing a limited form of curbing overseas trading of the rupiah would also help in curbing speculation on the local unit. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw7t007ao\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
