\par\par \b \uc2  Provinces to get 61.5% of revenue. \b0\par\par\uc2 975 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 July 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  MANADO, N. Sulawesi (JP): Provincial and district administrations will get more than 61.5 percent of the government's total domestic revenue next year when the laws on regional autonomy and intergovernment \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  balance become effective, Minister of Finance Bambang Sudibyo said here on Saturday. \par \par \uc2  Bambang told local officials at a briefing conference on preparations for the implementation of the two laws that domestic revenue for the 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year beginning in January was estimated at Rp 230 trillion (US$25.5 billion at the current exchange rate). \par \par \uc2  "However, only about Rp 112 trillion of the total revenue will be available for routine and development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  because Rp 79 trillion will go on servicing domestic and foreign debts and Rp 39 trillion on fuel and electricity \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Rp 69 trillion of the Rp 112 trillion will be allocated to provincial and district administrations under the intergovernment \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  law and only about Rp 43 trillion will be retained by the central government," the finance minister added. \par \par \uc2  He reiterated that the central government's financial capacity would be severely restrained as the bulk of revenue would be allocated to regional administrations. \par \par \uc2  Law No. 22/1999 gives more autonomy to local administrations and Law No. 25/1999 provides a bigger share of revenue to the provinces and districts. \par \par \uc2  However, he added that the estimated domestic revenue was only a preliminary figure which had yet to be finalized before the 2001 draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be proposed to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  in October. \par \par \uc2  The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is only from April to December as the government will base its \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year on the calendar year beginning in 2001. \par \par \uc2  Head of \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  analysis at the Ministry of Finance Marwanto Hardjowirjono told the same conference that the government expected to further lower its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year is estimated at 4.8 percent of gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  "It may be somewhere around 3 percent, because the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery next year is widely expected to be much stronger," Marwanto added. \par \par \uc2  The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  envisages total domestic revenue at Rp 152 trillion and a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at Rp 44 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Marwanto said that the preliminary revenue estimates for 2001 assumed a 3 percent to 4 percent inflation rate, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 3 percent to 4 percent and a range of Rp 6,800 to Rp 7,800 for the rupiah's exchange rate against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  Asked whether the assumption for the rupiah rate was too optimistic, he argued that the range was reached after considering macroeconomic factors only. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been on a downward trend since May, heavily fluctuating along with the country's political situation. \par \par \uc2  But Marwanto said it was impossible to measure political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , let alone factoring them into predictions for the rate of the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "We don't see any \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reasons that would justify a weaker rupiah rate," he said. \par \par \uc2  Marwanto added that the preliminary revenue estimate had not yet factored in the likely impact of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws, which were approved by the House last week. \par \par \uc2  The amended income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, for example, requires the government to allocate 20 percent of individual income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts to provinces. \par \par \uc2  The revised \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws, notably those on income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and general rules on \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , are designed mainly to broaden the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  base, strengthen \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection and improve \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration. \par \par \uc2  He said that similar to the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would also be covered by foreign loans, the privatization of state enterprises and the sales of assets under the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA). \par \par \uc2  "But we have yet make to an estimation of revenues from these sources," he added. \par \par \uc2  IBRA, a unit of the finance ministry, controls about Rp 600 trillion in assets taken over from closed down and nationalized banks. \par \par \uc2  But economist and secretary of the National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Council Sri Mulyani Indrawati said that pressure on the rupiah would still be strong next year, regardless of the political situation. \par \par \uc2  She said the government's plan to further hike fuel prices later this year was bound to increase inflation and subsequently weaken the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Further down the line, she said, any rise in inflation would also affect bank \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and this in turn would increase the government's servicing of its bonds (worth about Rp 430 trillion) issued to finance bank recapitalization. \par \par \uc2  "Let's not forget that we have domestic debts of Rp 600 trillion, most of which are in treasury bonds with \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  floating on the banking \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she warned. \par \par \uc2  The higher inflation rate would, therefore, burden the payment of these bonds, she said. \par \par \uc2  "We hope that the increase in income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue as a domestic funding source will be significant," Sri added. \par \par \uc2  Director General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Machfud Siddik said he expected to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue to between Rp 165 trillion and Rp 170 trillion in the next \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, from Rp 101 trillion in the current nine-month \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Although the amended income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law offers a break to many individual taxpayers, Machfud is optimistic about his target. \par \par \uc2  "The amended income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law, and other \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws, merely act as an umbrella for \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. The modernization of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration and efficiency of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection is more important," he added. \par \par \uc2  His office, he said, would go all out to net more eligible taxpayers and taxable objects. \par \par \uc2  Machfud expected that within five years, the number of registered individual taxpayers in the country would double or triple from the current 1.3 million. \par \par \uc2  "We estimate that there are 12 million potential individual taxpayers, but in the last 10 years the number of registered individual taxpayers increased by only 60 percent from about 800,000 in 1990," Machfud said. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw7v0072o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
