nt's management was very weak but he hoped Gus Dur (President Wahid's popular name) could change this condition. \par \par \uc2  He said what Gus Dur had delivered to the MPR plenary session on Monday was not a progress report on the first 10 months of his administration but a general statement of opinions on existing facts. \par \par \uc2  "What was expected from him was clear outlines of his afministration's policies to handle the existing problems, not a statement of opinions. That is not the duty of the president but of observers'," Haz said. \par \par \uc2  In contrast to PPP' s view, two MPR members of the Golkar Party faction said the presidnet's report contained positive points which needed to be realistically understood. \par \par \uc2  "There were many weaknesses. But one positive point we need to understand is that the president now realizes the importance of self-correction and learning from the past to improve the (government's) performance," Slamet Effendy Yusuf said. \par \par \uc2  Among the weaknesses of the president's progress report was the absence of comprehensive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  data, said Yusuf, who is known as a former activist of the Nahdlatul Ulama (NU), the Moslem mass organization Wahid once led. \par \par \uc2  Yusuf's fellow party member, La Ode Djeni, said the head of state had \par \par \uc2  realized his limited capability and falsehood. \par \par \uc2  "We wait for how (his government's) performance and next year's progress \par \par \uc2  report are because every party (the government and MPR-ed) can learn from each \par \par \uc2  other," he said. \par \par \uc2  La Ode also touched on the fact that the progress report was read by Cabinet \par \par \uc2  Secretary Marsilam Simanjuntak instead of Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri. \par \par \uc2  He said he had noted strains in the relations between  the president and his \par \par \uc2  vice president. "This is the second time (the president's speech was not delivered by Megawati) after the MPR plenary session last July 20 when the president came to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  to answer questions about the sacking of two cabinet ministers. \par \par \uc2  The MPR has 700 members. Of the total number, 182 are from the former ruling Golkar Party. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dw87005ny\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
