\par\par \b \uc2  FRIDAY'S EDITORIALS IN INDONESIA'S MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 1,035 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 August 2000\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  The bomb season has now been declared open in Jakarta, and who knows, perhaps other big cities and towns will also be forced to accept this unpleasant reality. The days when bombs failed to detonate or ended up in embarrasing thuds is over. \par \par \uc2  Well-heeled Indonesians, who stand to face certain risk from this attack, seem to have shown too much excitement about it, although they have tried to protect themselves by constructing strong entrance and exit points in the lanes leading to their mainsions. Pistol dealers too, have reported a brisk sale in firearms now that many wealthy Indonesians have decided to purchase weapons. \par \par \uc2  It is expected that the latest bomb attack will change the lifestyle of the rich to a certain extent. They are now advised to avoid busy shopping centres, or hotel lobbies, which are favorit places of terrorist when it comes to hiding their bombs. \par \par \uc2  Maybe it's time we all adopted the presidential maxim of not allowing \par \par \uc2  yourself to become easily excited by trivial matters. \par \par \uc2  Perhaps President Abdurrahman Wahid might just have a sound basis for his \par \par \uc2  much-quoted philosophy. If we think about it, an upsurge of foreign tourists in Indonesia and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of over four percent, is nothing to be sneezeed at. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  ABDURRAHMAN'S ACCOUNT \par \par \uc2  Indonesians all over the country can draw a breath of relief. President Abdurrahman Wahid's progress report of his first year in office appeared to be received well enough, if not enthusiastically, by the People's Consultatives Assembly (MPR). \par \par \uc2  In all of this, it is fair to remember that Abdurrahman inherited a host of \par \par \uc2  hugely complicated problems from the previous New Order regime. \par \par \uc2  With some handsight, it may be said that his major shortcoming has been not \par \par \uc2  his inability to govern, but rather his erratic style of leadership and his penchant for making controversial statements create unnecessary political complications that upset the market and have cost him at least part of his support from his coalition partners in the cabinet. \par \par \uc2  The president's appearance before the MPR yesterday leaves him with a chance \par \par \uc2  to improve his performance over the coming year. \par \par \uc2  The upcoming reshuffle of the cabinet, which Abdurrahman promised to the \par \par \uc2  MPR, could indicate whether he has really managed to improve his style of leadership. Let's hope it's true. Otherwise, he may well be facing similar hurdles to the ones he is facing now at next year's annual session of the Assembly. \par \par \uc2  By the time, the political landscape may have changed in a manner that may not be favorable for him. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  Editorial: CONGLOMERATES' ASSETS ADD TO \b \highlight22\uc2 UNCERTAINTY\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  An interesting talk show was aired last week, when Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie discussed the issue on Master Settlement and Acquisition Agreement (MSAA) with stock market observer, Lin Che Wei, and lawyer, Maqdir Ismail. \par \par \uc2  Based on the agreement, debtors could be saved from criminal indictment if \par \par \uc2  they hand over their assets. \par \par \uc2  For the Salim Group, it shall have settled its debts once the Indonesian \par \par \uc2  Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) sells its assets. \par \par \uc2  The case of the group however is complicated as there is a wide gap between \par \par \uc2  its total debts, worth Rp 52.6 trillion, and the value of its assets, estimated \par \par \uc2  at Rp 20 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Maqdir Ismail said conglomerates should be praised because they are willing \par \par \uc2  to hand over their assets. \par \par \uc2  But Kwik pointed out that the fall of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was caused by \par \par \uc2  bad conglomerates who used the people's money for their personal interests. \par \par \uc2  He reiterated that there is no plan to lift the MSAA but he raised a \par \par \uc2  question to legislators, whether they have agreed to cover these conglomerates' \par \par \uc2  debts. \par \par \uc2  Obviously, the people are not willing to shoulder the conglomerates' debts. \par \par \uc2  They would rather see these debtors put to jail. \par \par \uc2  Considering its gravity, the problem on the debts of conglomerates need to \par \par \uc2  be settled immediately as it could affect other \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  issues. \par \par \uc2  The restructurization of private debts is a factor which could add to the \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country, apart from bank recapitalization, although \par \par \uc2  there are other factors, such as legal certainty and security. \par \par \uc2  Positive macroeconomic indicators and increased consumption could be used as \par \par \uc2  foundations to revive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . - Kompas \par \par \uc2  Editorial: COURT OF PEOPLE'S REPRESENTATIVES \par \par \uc2  The annual session of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), which is feared to become a new disaster, has begun. The fear that there will be huge demonstrations, mass mobilizations and devastating horizontal conflicts, has not been proven true, at least on the first day of the 12-day event. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid, Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri, Speaker of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Akbar Tandjung, and MPR chairman, Amien Rais, shook hands with one another. They smiled and exchanged jokes. The four figures, widely supposed to represent interest groups, looked calm and peaceful. \par \par \uc2  The essence of this annual session is actually a court for all, especially for those who have wielded power but have not been able to resolve problems peacefully. Those who are given the authority but could not govern. Those who are tasked to monitor but have no power to do the duty. Those who should be on guard but instead trigger unrests. \par \par \uc2  Thus, the people's representatives who are present in the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  assembly building, do not judge anyone else but themselves. Sirs, who are currently deliberating, would be part of the problem if they do not want to be called "masterminds". \par \par \uc2  Sirs who call themselves the people's representatives are part of the power \par \par \uc2  game that has broken the peace in Maluku, Irian Jaya and Aceh. \par \par \uc2  If you are not the masterminds, your sins are your inability to resolve the \par \par \uc2  country's problems.  You are the defendants. \par \par \uc2  So that the people would no longer be victimized by the power game whipped \par \par \uc2  up by those who are currently attending the annual MPR session, this year's meeting must find a solution and not add to the list of new problems. That is why, one thing that need be approved is our common idea as a nation. Without it, this annual MPR session would be misleading. - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dw88005oo\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\pi