\par\par \b \uc2  Cabinet reshuffle crucial to improving performance. \b0\par\par\uc2 750 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 August 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): President Abdurrahman Wahid must reshuffle his discredited Cabinet to improve the performance of his administration, particularly on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  front, economists said. \par \par \uc2  An economist from the Centre for Strategic and International Studies, Pande Raja Silalahi, said want of an effective \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team was one of the major weaknesses of the current administration. \par \par \uc2  "The problem has been in the absence of a solid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team. So a Cabinet reshuffle is a must," Pande said. \par \par \uc2  He stressed that the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team must be filled with professionals not affiliated with any political party. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman said on Monday in his progress report to the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) that he planned another Cabinet shake-up. The President did not provide any details of the plan, but there has been speculation the reshuffle would take place later this month. \par \par \uc2  Critics have said the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers have performed poorly in attempting to resolve the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. There also have been suggestions the ministers are more devoted to their respected political parties than to the President. \par \par \uc2  "There was a clear acknowledgement in the President's speech that the performance of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers has not been optimal," said Gadjah Mada University economist Sri Adiningsih. "And to avoid widespread dissatisfaction among the people, a Cabinet reshuffle is needed." \par \par \uc2  Sri also said the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers should be independent and professional to ensure full loyalty to the President. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, an economist at a state-owned securities firm said word of the impending Cabinet reshuffle was not new to the financial market. \par \par \uc2  "The market is now waiting to see who will fill the posts. The market wants professional people," he said. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Kwik Kian Gie said he was prepared to step aside if the President chose to dismiss him. \par \par \uc2  He said a Cabinet reshuffle was the prerogative of the President. "I'm ready to be reshuffled," he added. \par \par \uc2  Kwik is a senior official with the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan), the largest party in the legislature. It is not clear whether the President has spoken with Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri, the chairwoman of PDI Perjuangan, about a Cabinet reshuffle. \par \par \uc2  The recent dismissal of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers Laksamana Sukardi, another PDI Perjuangan official, and Jusuf Kalla, a member of Golkar Party, has been condemned by legislators from the two parties, adding to the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding Abdurrahman's presidency. \par \par \uc2  In a related development, Minister of Mines and Energy Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono said he was unaware of any plans by the President to appoint him "first minister". \par \par \uc2  "I have heard about the rumor, but I don't know anything about it," the retired Army lieutenant-general said. \par \par \uc2  There have been rumors Abdurrahman will create the powerful "first minister" post to help him run his administration. People also say this move would help the President win the backing of the military. \par \par \uc2  In other matters, Abdurrahman also said in his progress report that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had emerged from its worst crisis in decades but the recovery was still in its early stages and had yet to gain strength. \par \par \uc2  He admitted the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  gains during his 10 months in office were relatively small. The President said that looking ahead, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery would be based on four main pillars: macroeconomic stability, empowerment of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  institutions, structural \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform and protection of the poor. \par \par \uc2  The President also said the government would remain committed to implementing the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program agreed to with the International Monetary Fund. \par \par \uc2  The IMF signed an agreement with the current administration in January to provide some US$5 billion to help finance the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, traders said the market responded positively to the President's apology for the performance of his administration. \par \par \uc2  After trading at an intraday high of Rp 8,725 to the U.S. dollar, the rupiah ended at Rp 8,630 against the dollar in late trading on Monday. However, this was still lower than its Rp 8,608 close on Friday. \par \par \uc2  The President told the 700-member Assembly, the country's highest \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body, that he would learn from his past mistakes. The apology is seen as an attempt to reduce the opposition to his administration. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah dropped to a 21-month low of Rp 9,570 per dollar last month amid political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the Assembly's 10-day Annual Session that began on Monday. (rei/bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 200