\par\par \b \uc2  Faulting the  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  record. \b0\par\par\uc2 710 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 August 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Most analysts and factions at the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) criticized President Abdurrahman Wahid for his unsatisfactory record in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  field and complained that his progress report on Monday was completely devoid of any strategic goals, let alone a viable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  vision. \par \par \uc2  Even though the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has started to pick up slowly since early this year, growing 3.2 percent in the first quarter and 4.13 percent in the second quarter from the corresponding period last year, the nascent recovery is seen as quite fragile. It will not be sustainable for long without the new investment activities that remain depressed due to political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and extreme lack of law enforcement and security. \par \par \uc2  Enthusiasm about the budding recovery was further dampened by the steep depreciation of the rupiah since May, weakening from Rp 7,400 to the U.S. dollar in January to around Rp 8,700 at present, thereby creating stronger inflationary pressure and forcing the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to raise its benchmark interest rate from as low as 11 percent in February to more than 13.50 percent. \par \par \uc2  Even though the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  achievements are still way below what people expected, given the strong legitimacy of his government, it is really not fair to simply reject Abdurrahman's progress report to the Assembly as wholly devoid of strategic goals to bring the nation out of its current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  predicament. Though an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  vision was not clearly outlined in his report, one can infer clear strategic objectives, which form his vision on how to lead the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to a sustainable robust growth. \par \par \uc2  Most importantly, the President reaffirmed his strong commitment to macroeconomic stability, continuation of structural efforts, the market \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as well as autonomy of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He demonstrated a full grasp of the fundamental weaknesses besetting the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  by selecting four pillars to underpin sustainable and just \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the future: macroeconomic stability; strengthening of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  institutions; improvement of structural policies; and the empowerment of the poor. \par \par \uc2  It was obviously impossible for the President to provide in his report all the details on what the government would do as he had to cover all the sectors in the 35-page speech. But then one cannot obtain the right and full perspective on his policies and achievements by perusing only his address. The progress report should be analyzed along with the memorandum of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial policies attached to the government's letter of intent to the International Monetary Fund dated July 31. \par \par \uc2  The 23-page memorandum stipulates in detail programs and strategic objectives until 2002 in the four pillars of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development cited in the President's progress report. It elaborates efforts to maintain macroeconomic stability through prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary management. Its \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, for example, clearly address the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization, and clearly set targets with time tables. \par \par \uc2  The President is fully right in citing weak institutions as one of the fundamental weaknesses that caused the current multidimensional crisis. Empirical studies in many countries have clearly concluded that the quality of institutions also affects \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth as the institutional framework influences the cost of transactions and transformation (production process). \par \par \uc2  The memorandum elaborates on programs to strengthen institutions through corporate and banking restructuring and the enhancement of good governance in the private and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sectors. Also integral in these programs are the audits of major state companies with strategic roles in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as those operating in utility and upstream industries. No less than 62 state enterprises have been identified to be independently audited by 2001 in view of diagnosing their problems and devising efforts to strengthen their operations. \par \par \uc2  All these programs, though appearing separate and unrelated to each other, have the same strategic objective of building up strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  institutions in the private and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sectors, which are crucial for sustainable growth. \par \par \uc2  But again all these programs and their target timetables are stated policies that have yet to be executed. Hence, the upcoming Cabinet reshuffle, which will predictably cover mostly \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  portfolios, should bring in a strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team. The market will continue to punish the nation's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  if the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team does not consist of highly credible and competent personalities. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw8a0071m\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
