\par\par \b \uc2  BI official expects SBI rate to fall this week. \b0\par\par\uc2 479 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 August 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  senior deputy governor Anwar Nasution expects the benchmark interest rate on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory notes to decrease at the weekly auction on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Anwar said the condition was ripe for the interest rate to drop. \par \par \uc2  "There have been signs for the (SBI) interest rate to drop," Anwar announced following a meeting with senior \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers. \par \par \uc2  "We hope that the condition continues to improve so that the interest rate can further decrease," he added. \par \par \uc2  He said the near completion of the country's bank recapitalization program was crucial to reducing \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The government has completed the bank recapitalization program with the exception of Bank Bali, which is expected to be completed next month. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  allowed the benchmark interest rate to increase over the past couple of months amid the weakening of the rupiah. But the interest rate on one-month SBIs was unchanged last week at 13.52 percent. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said that the recent strengthening of the rupiah was a primary factor for \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to allow the interest rate to remain the same or decrease. \par \par \uc2  The interest rate on three-month SBIs dropped to 13.29 percent last week from 13.49 percent previously. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said earlier that it wanted to see the benchmark interest rate at about 12 percent by the end of this year. \par \par \uc2  A rise in SBI rates would increase the burden on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to finance the payment of interest on government bonds issued to help finance the country's bank recapitalization program. Some of the bonds carry variable \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  linked to SBI \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Asked on the direction of the rupiah, Anwar said that he expected the local currency to strengthen amid the improving domestic political climate. \par \par \uc2  "Looking at the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, there's no reason for the rupiah to weaken," he said. \par \par \uc2  Anwar said that the move by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to curb speculators by sending its inspectors to foreign exchange banks to make sure they abide by the existing prudential rulings had been effective in stabilizing the local unit. \par \par \uc2  Anwar warned recently that foreign currency dealers and bankers who violated the ruling would be deported. He added that local bankers found guilty would be banned from entering the country's banking industry for the rest of their lives. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been strengthening since Wednesday last week amid easing political tension between President Abdurrahman Wahid and the country's top legislators. \par \par \uc2  The local unit continued to strengthen on Monday to close higher at about Rp 8,200 per U.S. dollar in late trading compared to Rp 8,345 per dollar on Friday. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah dropped to a 21-month low of Rp 9,570 per dollar last month amid political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw8f007su\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
