\par\par \b \uc2  BI estimates inflation to exceed government target. \b0\par\par\uc2 650 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 August 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said on Wednesday that inflation would likely be at about 7.67 percent this year, exceeding the government's target of between 5 percent and 7 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said in its latest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  report that prices would be higher than initially expected due to the weakening of the rupiah and a planned increase in fuel prices later this year. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that the weakening of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar had increased the price of imported goods and raw materials. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah dropped to a 21-month low of 9,570 per U.S. dollar last month amid domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . But signs of easing political tension between President Abdurrahman Wahid and top legislators this month has helped the rupiah to strengthen to about Rp 8,300 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  The government had adopted an exchange rate of Rp 7,000 per dollar for this year. \par \par \uc2  A reduction in fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  is planned for October, which will cause fuel prices to increase. That increase will raise the cost of transportation and prices of manufactured products. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  also predicted that inflation in 2001 would range between 6 percent and 8 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has allowed the benchmark interest rate of its one-month \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes (SBIs) to increase for the past several weeks to help the ailing rupiah and curb inflationary pressure. \par \par \uc2  The benchmark interest rate move higher to 13.56 percent at an auction on Wednesday, compared to 13.52 percent last week. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials earlier said that they wanted to see the benchmark interest rate at about 12 percent by the end of this year. \par \par \uc2  On the rupiah, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  forecast that the local unit would strengthen to between 7,780 to 8,200 per dollar in the July to September period. \par \par \uc2  It also said that the rupiah would strengthen to between Rp 6,500 and Rp 7,000 to the dollar next year. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah weakened slightly to 8,348 per dollar on Wednesday, compared to 8,315 on Tuesday as investors awaited the result of the upcoming Cabinet reshuffle, details of which are scheduled to be announced on Monday. \par \par \uc2  On the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  maintained its initial forecast of 3 percent to 4 percent growth in gross domestic product (GDP) this year. \par \par \uc2  But the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would grow higher next year at between 4 percent to 5 percent. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  contracted by more than 13 percent in 1998 when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis deepened and grew by 0.2 percent last year. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that exports were projected to increase to US$14.13 billion in the third quarter, from $13.88 billion in the second quarter of this year. \par \par \uc2  It added that imports were also expected to rise to $8.72 billion in the third quarter from $8.3 billion in the second quarter. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that current account surplus was expected to shrink to $1.29 billion in the July to September period from $1.34 billion in the previous quarter as import growth would exceed export growth. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the third quarter would be equal to 7.1 months of imports, higher than 6.8 months of imports in the second quarter. \par \par \uc2  Total investment was expected to grow by between 1 percent and 2 percent this year and jump to between 5.5 percent and 6.5 percent next year, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said. \par \par \uc2  It said that the resumption in bank lending would help increase the amount of total investment both by the private and government sectors. \par \par \uc2  Total investment dropped by 20 percent last year. \par \par \uc2  The government has almost completed the country's bank restructuring and recapitalization program, allowing banks to resume lending, albeit in relatively small volumes.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw8i006kc\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
