's pay attention to this in the next three or four months. If they could not work together the people of Indonesia would have to pay the price very dearly." In yet another development on Thursday, economist Edi Suandi Hamid from the Indonesian Islamic University in Yogyakarta said \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery \par \par \uc2  efforts woul be bogged down by the danger of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  opinion that the cabinet would be eliminated by the country's big political forces not properly \par \par \uc2  represented in the government. \par \par \uc2  "Investors would need to wait a long time pending restoration of the situation before they would ever think about channeling their capital in again. And consequently \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  will linger on." Joining the choir of anxious experts, Surabaya-based Mangara Tambunan said ther cabinet should have a well focused agenda with due consideration of the implementation of regional autonomy law as well as the free trade era. \par \par \uc2  In his view, the cabinet has two main duties, one is to expedite bank recapitalization process and the other is to reinvigorate industries in the real sector. \par \par \uc2  The capability of such ministers as Bungaran Saragih, he said, should not be doubted. He had all along defended common people even before being \par \par \uc2  appointed minister. \par \par \uc2  He also said that on the whole the cabinet would redefine its relations with the IMF. And by the same token realization of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery programs may be \par \par \uc2  a lot more difficult now. (tb/mrp/aac/ard/iz). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dw8o000ow\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
