\par\par \b \uc2  Chief  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  minister upbeat on rupiah. \b0\par\par\uc2 819 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 August 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The newly-appointed Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Rizal Ramli expects the rupiah to further strengthen against the U.S. dollar this year. \par \par \uc2  Rizal said on Saturday that he was optimistic that the rupiah would return to a reasonable value of between Rp 7,500-Rp 8,000 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  "With the initiatives and steps that will be taken, we're optimistic the rupiah will stabilize," he told the press at his office following the inauguration of the new Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  He also said that his office would improve cooperation with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  in order to maintain macroeconomic and monetary stability. \par \par \uc2  After rising to a three-month high of around Rp 8,090 per dollar, the rupiah suddenly plunged to around Rp 8,365 late on Wednesday following the announcement of the new Cabinet line-up. \par \par \uc2  Some have expressed fear that the rupiah could plunge to around Rp 10,000 per dollar due to the political instability created by the controversy surrounding the new Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  The markets are concerned because the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDIP) of Vice President Megawati Sukarnoputri as well as other large political parties have not been proportionately represented in the Cabinet. \par \par \uc2  The new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team was not as had been expected by the financial markets, particularly as regards the appointment of Prijadi Praptosuhardjo as the new Finance Minister. Prijadi had earlier failed to pass the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's "fit and proper test" for him to lead the state-owned Bank Rakyat Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Rizal reiterated that the negative response of the financial markets was only a temporary phenomenon. He was optimistic that if the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team could prove that it was solid and effective, confidence would return. \par \par \uc2  "All of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers are determined to create a solid team," Rizal said. \par \par \uc2  He added that he would ask all members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team to refrain from debating government \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  outside the meeting room as such action would only create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The debate must only be carried on in the meeting room," he said. \par \par \uc2  Abdurrahman's previous \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team had been criticized for its lack of teamwork and its ineffectiveness. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah ended relatively flat at Rp 8,380 per dollar on Friday, while the Jakarta Stock Exchange composite index ended up 0.9 percent at 486.907 points. \par \par \uc2  Currency and stock traders said that the statement by Megawati that she would not resign, despite reports that she was disappointed with the new Cabinet lineup, helped improve overall confidence in the financial markets. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah tumbled to a 21-month low of Rp 9,570 per dollar earlier this month due primarily to the political instability created by a rift among members of the country's political elite. \par \par \uc2  The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumes an exchange rate of Rp 7,000 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  Rizal was also optimistic about the prospects for the current April-December 2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  given, particularly, current high oil prices. \par \par \uc2  He said that although certain revenue targets were lagging behind, the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team would work harder to achieve these targets during the remainder of the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. \par \par \uc2  "We still have room for maneuver," he said. \par \par \uc2  Several analysts had earlier expressed concern that the state revenue targets from the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) and privatization program might not be fulfilled. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has been targeted to raise Rp 18.9 trillion (US$2.28 billion) this year, but so far the agency has only raised some Rp 7.9 trillion in cash. \par \par \uc2  The government has also targeted the privatization of some nine state-owned enterprises this year to raise Rp 6.5 trillion in proceeds, but these privatizations have not taken place so far. \par \par \uc2  Asked about his plans with the controversial Master Settlement and Acquisition Agreement (MSAA), Rizal said that he would continue the "good \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 " of his predecessor Kwik Kian Gie. \par \par \uc2  "But I will wait for input from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  first before formulating a new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  The House has formed an investigation team to decide whether to agree to the plans proposed by the previous \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team led by Kwik to revise the MSAA. \par \par \uc2  The MSAA is an agreement made by the previous administration of president B.J. Habibie with several top bankers to repay their debts to the government. \par \par \uc2  But Kwik demanded a revision of the agreement as implementing it in full could result in the government suffering huge losses. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Kwik said on Saturday that he would now become a member of the legislature and would criticize and provide alternatives to government \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies which he deemed to be inappropriate. \par \par \uc2  "If I disagree with a certain \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , I will criticize it and suggest an alternative," Kwik said on the sidelines of the Cabinet inauguration ceremony. \par \par \uc2  Kwik declined to comment on the MSAA issue, saying that it was a complex matter. (rei/prb) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw8r00685\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
