\par\par \b \uc2  Soeharto trial venue rocked. \b0\par\par\uc2 1,249 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 August 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The South Jakarta District Court is due to begin the long-awaited trial of former president Soeharto on Thursday amid more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  following an explosion adjacent to the trial venue late on Wednesday night. \par \par \uc2  A parked yellow Koantas Bima city bus was left mangled by the explosion. No casualties were reported and there was also little damage to surrounding buildings. \par \par \uc2  The bus was parked in front of the Mitra Karya auto repair shop on Jl. Taman Marga Satwa, South Jakarta, about 300 meters across the street from the Ministry of Agriculture compound, where the trial will be held. \par \par \uc2  Witnesses said they heard the explosion at about 10:00 p.m., describing it as a "great thundering sound" which alarmed residents and brought them into the hitherto quiet street. \par \par \uc2  Jakarta Police chief of detectives Snr. Supt. Harry Montolalu said he believed an explosive device planted under one of the seats on the left side of the front of the bus caused the explosion. \par \par \uc2  "We believe it was a large amount of firecrackers wrapped in newspaper, but its (explosive power) was still below TNT level," he said adding that the bus was empty when the explosion occurred. \par \par \uc2  The blast blew a hole in the roof and floor of the vehicle, and shattered all the windows. Tiny pieces of newspaper were sprinkled about the bus. \par \par \uc2  According to Harry, the bus driver, Bafri, had parked and left the bus, which serves the Kampung Rambutan-Lebak Bulus route, just before 10:00 p.m. to get something to eat, after which he planned to go home. \par \par \uc2  Approximately 10 to 15 minutes later, the explosion occurred. \par \par \uc2  Both Bafri and Leman, the owner of the auto repair shop, were being questioned by the South Jakarta Police. \par \par \uc2  Abdul Muis, a high school student who lives in the area, said the bus was often parked in the vicinity at that time. \par \par \uc2  Wilman Sembiring, 42, a mechanic based next to the Mitra Karya repair shop said he was working underneath a car when the explosion occurred. \par \par \uc2  Wilman, who was about a dozen meters away, said the explosion was loud but the ground did not shake. \par \par \uc2  Harry acknowledged that the attack was part of an act of terror, but stressed that it might be going too far to connect it with the impending Soeharto trial. \par \par \uc2  Just after midnight, the bus had been taken away by police for further forensics tests. \par \par \uc2  By 1 a.m. on Thursday morning, no information was immediately available on whether the trial would be affected by the explosion. \par \par \uc2  Soeharto \par \par \uc2  This latest incident adds further \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  to a trial some doubt will even see the presence of the defendant, Soeharto. \par \par \uc2  "I doubt Pak Harto will attend Thursday's hearing ... he's not capable at all," Juan Felix Tampubolon, one of Soeharto's defense attorneys, said on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  "I have personally tried explaining to him the substance of the trial. I can see that he is trying very hard to understand what I am saying ... but he just cannot comprehend. He can't put even his own thoughts into words," Juan said. \par \par \uc2  Sources close to the investigation said there would be a meeting on Wednesday evening at Soeharto's residence in Menteng, Central Jakarta, to discuss the matter. \par \par \uc2  Juan said that the medical team would arrive at the residence of the ailing 79-year-old defendant at 7 a.m. on Thursday morning to conduct an examination. \par \par \uc2  "After examining him, the medical team will declare whether my client is fit to attend the hearing or not," he said. \par \par \uc2  Juan added that the hearing would not proceed if Soeharto was not there in person to hear the charges read. \par \par \uc2  "The charges cannot be read in the absence of the defendant. The idea is that even if he is present, but is not mentally fit to be examined by the court, then his presence becomes useless," he said, referring to the Criminal Code Procedures (KUHAP). \par \par \uc2  Juan and Soeharto's other lawyers: Muhammad Assegaf, Otto Cornelius Kaligis, Indriyanto Seno Adji, Denny Kailimang, Victor Siregar and Syamsu Hadi came on Wednesday to inspect the chosen venue for the hearing at the auditorium of the Ministry of Agriculture in South Jakarta. \par \par \uc2  Soeharto is alleged to have misused some Rp 1.4 trillion and some US$416 million of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds in the seven charitable foundations he chaired. He faces charges of stealing state money by funneling it from \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -free charity foundations he ran into the businesses of family and friends. \par \par \uc2  At least 100 police officers are guarding the venue around the clock and a truck mounted water cannon and an armored car are on standby. \par \par \uc2  City Police said earlier that at least 400 men would be deployed in and around the venue. \par \par \uc2  City Police chief Insp. Gen. Nurfaizi, who inspected the venue on Wednesday, said maximum security would be provided for spectators. \par \par \uc2  As of Wednesday, South Jakarta District Court workers were still preparing the venue, while police officers had already installed metal detectors at the main entrance. \par \par \uc2  Despite promises made by South Jakarta District Court chief Lalu Mariyun, TV screens have yet to be installed in certain spots around the ministry for spectators not accommodated in the courtroom. \par \par \uc2  Inside the auditorium, district court workers have completed installing a raised platform on which the bench is set, while the prosecutors' desk and dozens of wooden benches for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  have been put in place. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, Coordinating Minister for Political, Social and Security Affairs Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono said on Wednesday that negotiations for the return of some of former president Soeharto's wealth had been temporarily halted. \par \par \uc2  "The negotiation is halted to give way to the legal process," Susilo told reporters after attending a plenary session at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said the negotiation was part of the nation's effort to overcome the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis although it would not neglect the legal process against the former president. \par \par \uc2  Susilo admitted to having met Soeharto's family twice for the negotiation. \par \par \uc2  Separately, law experts called on the state prosecutors to be tough and able to produce evidence to support the corruption charges, while the judges hearing the case must maintain their integrity. \par \par \uc2  Pontang Moerad, a criminal law expert at Padjadjaran University in Bandung, said on Wednesday the prosecutors must be well prepared. "They must have sufficient evidence and appropriate witnesses." \par \par \uc2  He said both the prosecutors and the panel of judges must be strong enough to stand up to political and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  pressure. \par \par \uc2  Artidjo Alkostar from Yogyakarta's Islamic University of Indonesia said the judges must be able to maintain their integrity and respect the principle of law. \par \par \uc2  He warned that Soeharto's trial would become the yardstick by which the country's law enforcement and judiciary would be measured. \par \par \uc2  Artidjo, a candidate to become the chief justice of the Supreme Court, said the panel of judges would receive political pressure and also would likely be offered bribes. \par \par \uc2  "They must have the courage to reject any bribery offers. On the other hand, the judges can not favor the government's interests or bow to \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  pressure," he said. \par \par \uc2  All the experts said one of the main problems in the trial was that Soeharto already was seen as guilty in many circles. Both the prosecutors and the judges must have the courage to say "guilty" if the defendant is guilty, and to exonerate him if he is innocent, they said. (ylt/jun/25/44/sur) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw8v006s2\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Prajogo seeks Marubeni-style debt restructuring treatment. \b0\par\par\uc2 586 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 September 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Previous owners of PT Chandra Asri Petrochemical Center (CAPC) has asked that they be given the same government treatment as that given to Marubeni Corp. This was revealed by an IBRA spokesman during interview with Bisnis yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Amir Sambodo, Adviser to the chairman of IBRA, said during negotiations with CAPC owners, Prajogo Pangestu, one of the company's Shareholders proposed that the company's debt restructuring scheme should be the same as that of Marubeni. \par \par \uc2  The official said negotiations were still underway and there has yet to be an agreement on handing over of the company's majority share ownership to IBRA. \par \par \uc2  Marubeni and IBRA had in early June this year signed an agreement under which the former agreed to extend to 12 years the maturity period of Japanese loans to CAPC worth US$600 million with a 2.5% interest above LIBOR while a further US$100 million would be converted into capital. \par \par \uc2  For its part, IBRA would convert all its loans to Chandra Asri into capital and by this the composition of share ownership of the company would be 80% belonging to IBRA and 20% to Marubeni. \par \par \uc2  The agreed deal has yet to be legalized and for this there must first of all be an approval from Chandra Asri's previous owners. \par \par \uc2  IBRA's Deputy Chairman Irwan Siregar said Prajogo had for some time been asking for similar treatment. "Just wait in the next several days the negotiations on the technical aspects would be completed." \par \par \uc2  Amir had previously explained that IBRA would still need to find out the company's real share ownership composition. \par \par \uc2  If the assets handed over were not equal to the worth of its obligations a solution may be to set up a holding company like Holdiko to deal with the previous owners, he said. \par \par \uc2  He made the remark after learning about the results of a recent study by Deutsche Bank that Chandra Asri's sustainable debt was only worth US$400 million. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank has reportedly sent a letter to then coordinating minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , finance, and industry Kwik Kian Gie dated May 12, 200 asking for clarification on the company's sustainable debt issue. \par \par \uc2  Bisnis sources said the issue became so complicated after the government-appointed financial sector \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee (KKSK) approved CAPC's debt to equity proposal. Under this IBRA would control 80% of the company's ownership. \par \par \uc2  This in a way was a kind of short selling because the government then did not have any share in it, Amir said, adding IBRA thereby had no bargaining power any more. \par \par \uc2  In a related development a potential buyer has changed its mind and is no longer willing to buy IBRA's shares in Chandra Asri. \par \par \uc2  BP (formerly BP Amoco) is not interested due to the arduous settlement process of this matter. \par \par \uc2  It may still be willing to step in but not for a merger involving Chandra Asri, Peni, and Tri Polyta as yet because Peni is under BP anyway. \par \par \uc2  On \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that has developed following the appointment of Chandra Asri's top leader ECW Neloe as Bank Mandiri's President Director. Amir said the matter would be discussed during a general shareholders' meeting. \par \par \uc2  Petrochemical industry sources say President Abdurrahman Wahid and IBRA Chairman Cacuk Sudaryanto have agreed to nomination of Gunadharma Hartarto to Chandra Asri's CEO post but Marubeni rejected it. As a result, a former BRI director has been assigned to sit in as acting CEO. (yn/mt/ya). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dw91000qe\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
