\par\par \b \uc2  WEDNESDAY'S EDITORIALS IN INDONESIA'S MAJOR DAILIES. \b0\par\par\uc2 629 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 September 2000\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  PERMANENT CONFLICT \par \par \uc2  The case of East Timor is the enactment of a human drama in which Indonesia is torn by a conflict arising from its attempt to preserve its hold on that territory. It is also one in which it had to bow to international opinion. And so it was that East Timor was able to finally secede from Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The loss of East Timor has caused great anguish and has deeply hurt national feelings to such a point that many later accused Australia, among foreign countries, of machination aimed at terminating Indonesia's rule in that territory. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia as a sovereign state, has asked the United Nations for permission to try the Indonesian military and police personnel including the endented terror which led to killing of a great number of pro-independence East Timorese, and the scorched earth \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  which saw dozens of building and homes erupt into flames. \par \par \uc2  In Dili the churches were full with people seeking to express their gratitude that that they have now become independent. But on the border, East Timor generals who refuse to accept the changing situation are still aiming their guns at their brothers across the border. - The Indonesian Observer \par \par \uc2  INDONESIA INC. \par \par \uc2  The quick decision by the government to appoint a new supervisory chief for the 155 state companies should be welcomed as a move which will, at the least, immediately put an end to the atmosphere of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  which has prevailed ever since the disbandment of the ministry of state enterprises during the recent Cabinet reshuffle. But we remain skeptical as to whether the move will be sufficient to kick start a process of real reform in state companies. \par \par \uc2  The new chief economics minister, Rizal Ramli, announced early last week, or only two days after his installation, that he is now taking direct charge of state enterprises supervision, making him the fourth person to hold this position within a period of only 30 months. \par \par \uc2  Those who have followed the progress of state sector reform programs in the past are obviously dubious about the government's seriousness in improving the competitiveness of state enterprises. There are too many conflicts of interest and too many politically well-connected rent seekers competing with each other to milk the huge assets of the state sector. \par \par \uc2  We fear that Rizal in turn will also prove incapable of making any significant difference as long as the government, notably the President, is not really committed to providing state company managements with full operational (managerial) and financial autonomy within a framework of accountability. \par \par \uc2  State enterprises will remain inefficient and highly vulnerable to corruption and rent-seeking practices by those in power, thus adding to the inefficiency of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as a whole. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  "HUMAN CALCULATION" \par \par \uc2  Although the 12 percent fuel oil price hike is set to take effect in October, some trains and "stubborn" taxicabs have begun charging higher fares. \par \par \uc2  This means that business calculation has been done ahead of the proper calculation for consumers. In the end, the fare increase will only burden the people. However, ranking officials feel nothing about such difficulty. \par \par \uc2  What is worse is that a fare hike is never followed by an improvement in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  services. There is no reciprocal move between consumers as the fare hike "victims" and the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -maker, the government. \par \par \uc2  We must end the old way of treating the people as powerless \par \par \uc2  beings who seem to have no right. \par \par \uc2  Although the nation faces a lot of problems, the government \par \par \uc2  should begin improving the quality of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  services. \par \par \uc2  As doomsday has not yet come, the improvement of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  services \par \par \uc2  must be done right away. \par \par \uc2  Every price hike should not only reflect \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  calculation, \par \par \uc2  but "human calculation" as well. - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dw96000mn\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Manufacturing sector's stocks remain under selling pressure. \b0\par\par\uc2 314 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 September 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: Investors have yet to turn to manufacturing \par \par \uc2  sector's stocks. This was evident up to the end of \par \par \uc2  August. Many investors chose to sell rather than buy \par \par \uc2  the sector's stocks due to rupiah depreciation and \par \par \uc2  political jolts affecting the bourse last month. \par \par \uc2  Many investors would only sell for short-term gain \par \par \uc2  especially because of the national currency \par \par \uc2  depreciation which reached Rp8,290 per US dollar by \par \par \uc2  late August. \par \par \uc2  Political instability was also to blame for the lack \par \par \uc2  of enthusiasm over the stocks in this sector. \par \par \uc2  Many investors were worried about negative impact \par \par \uc2  that may result from the government's paln to hike \par \par \uc2  energy sector' prices as of October this year. \par \par \uc2  This sector is surely to be affected by the fuel price \par \par \uc2  hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Many companies would need to spend more \par \par \uc2  to cover operational cost. \par \par \uc2  Political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the slow pace of real sector \par \par \uc2  recovery are bound to exert pressure on the \par \par \uc2  performance of stocks in this sector. \par \par \uc2  Many foreign investors were known to have shifted \par \par \uc2  their capital to other Asian stock markets due to \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's domestic instability. Te country's bad \par \par \uc2  country risk rating is a big source of foreign \par \par \uc2  investors' concern. \par \par \uc2  Of the 10 big stocks in this sector, only two \par \par \uc2  registered gains, namely Astra (5.20%) and Kalbe \par \par \uc2  Farma (5.47%). The rest lost value. \par \par \uc2  A total of 633.521 million shares changed hands in \par \par \uc2  this sector worth Rp777 billion. \par \par \uc2  Nevertheless the stocks in this sector may perform \par \par \uc2  better this month due to the perception that the \par \par \uc2  government would perform better too. This would become \par \par \uc2  reality if the new cabinet could start solving \par \par \uc2  political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems which have caused a \par \par \uc2  great deal of concern to investors. \par \par \uc2  Investors wishing to book long-term profit should \par \par \uc2  start buying manufacturing sector's stocks from now \par \par \uc2  on. Future prospects are bright indeed. \par \par \uc2  * Sigma Research. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dw96000s5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
