\par\par \b \uc2  BI warns that inflation may exceed target. \b0\par\par\uc2 338 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 September 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  warned on Tuesday the inflation target for this year might be exceeded, with the recent weakening of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar and the planned increase in fuel prices seen as the main culprits. \par \par \uc2  But the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said in a statement issued following a meeting of its board of governors it would do its best to keep inflation under control. \par \par \uc2  "Looking at the recent developments, the board of governors perceives that the assumptions used in setting the inflation target for 2000 must be revised," the statement said. \par \par \uc2  The government has targeted an inflation level of between 5 percent and 7 percent for this year. \par \par \uc2  The Central Bureau of Statistics earlier warned inflation for the year could reach between 8 percent and 9 percent. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said the weakening of the rupiah against the dollar had inflated the cost of imported raw materials, and next month's planned 12 percent increase in fuel prices would be followed by increases in the price of goods and the cost of transportation. \par \par \uc2  The government has targeted an exchange rate of Rp 7,000 per U.S. dollar for the year, but the rupiah plunged to as low as Rp 8,900 per dollar in July due to political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The rupiah has been hovering near Rp 8,300 to the dollar in recent weeks. \par \par \uc2  "The board of governors will make various efforts to ensure that inflation is kept under control. \par \par \uc2  "The possibility of a further weakening of the rupiah should be carefully watched," \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said in the statement. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said it would continue its efforts to curb speculation in the local currency by enforcing prudential banking rulings. It also said it would continue to try to absorb excess liquidity. \par \par \uc2  "Efforts to increase the coordination between monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as well as other \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, must be continued in a bid to maintain monetary stability," \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dw96007tg\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
