he medium-term outlook." \par \par \uc2  It said renewed volatility and weakness in financial markets cloud the \par \par \uc2  outlook for Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "Market confidence is fragile, and private capital flows have yet to \par \par \uc2  recover," the IMF said. \par \par \uc2  The IMF welcomed Jakarta's plans to use increased oil revenues to reduce its \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but said more needs to be done in banking reform and other \par \par \uc2  structural measures. \par \par \uc2  It called for the government to divest its bank holdings acquired during the \par \par \uc2  crisis while strengthening supervisory systems. \par \par \uc2  In 1998 the IMF cobbled together a 46 billion dollar bail-out program for \par \par \uc2  Indonesia, tied to a staggered reform program, to help pull the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  out of the regional financial crisis. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dw9q002ay\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
