\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Budget \highlight\uc2  realistic, except rupiah assumption - Experts. \b0\par\par\uc2 756 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 October 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Experts said that the government's 2001 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal was generally quite realistic although legislators expressed skepticism on the exchange rate assumption. \par \par \uc2  "I think the figures (in the proposed \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) are quite realistic," said senior economist at PT Danareksa Securities Raden Pardede. \par \par \uc2  He cited the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth assumption of 4.5 percent, inflation at 7 percent, international oil price at US$22 per barrel and an exchange rate of Rp 7,300 per U.S. dollar next year as reasonable. \par \par \uc2  "There is actually nothing new because the figures are mostly as expected except on the non-oil and gas \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue target," Raden said. \par \par \uc2  The government envisaged total revenues of Rp 243 trillion, of which almost 70 percent would come from domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Out of the income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  target of more than Rp 93 trillion, more than Rp 75 trillion would come from the non-oil and gas sector. \par \par \uc2  "The government will have to work very very hard to meet this target," Raden said. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, several legislators said that the exchange rate assumption of Rp 7,300 per dollar in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft was "too optimistic." \par \par \uc2  "I think the exchange rate assumption is too optimistic given the current domestic political condition," House Speaker Akbar Tandjung said. \par \par \uc2  Akbar said if the domestic political condition remained \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , foreign investors would not enter the country and the rupiah would remain weak. \par \par \uc2  Separatist movements, communal and religious clashes, and conflicts between political elites have plagued the country since 1998. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah is currently hovering at around Rp 8,785 per dollar. \par \par \uc2  Former chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister Kwik Kian Gie, who is now a member of the House, also expressed doubt over the government's exchange rate assumption. \par \par \uc2  Kwik said it would be difficult to achieve the Rp 7,300 per dollar target because of the inflationary threat. \par \par \uc2  "If inflation is uncontrollable how can the government (stabilize) the rupiah," he said. \par \par \uc2  He pointed out that there had already been inflationary pressure even prior to the Oct. 1 fuel price increase. \par \par \uc2  The government increased fuel prices between 9 percent and 25 percent which many analysts said could trigger inflation. Analysts said that inflation this year could rise to more than 9 percent, higher than the government's target of between 5 percent and 7 percent. \par \par \uc2  The government is also planning to increase fuel prices by another 20 percent in April in a bid to help reduce the burden on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  But Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli said that the government had yet to decide whether it would raise the fuel prices again. \par \par \uc2  "It is still an open option," he said. \par \par \uc2  Kwik observed that the other macroeconomic assumptions in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft were realistic. \par \par \uc2  He said that the first half \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance this year should provide the "momentum" for further \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and macroeconomic stability in the second half and next year. \par \par \uc2  But Kwik warned that the government must work to maintain the "momentum." \par \par \uc2  "But if the (domestic) security problems are not resolved immediately, don't expect the momentum to be maintained," he said. \par \par \uc2  "The government must realize that security, social and political conditions are closely linked to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability," he added. \par \par \uc2  He cautioned that the government should not rely solely on the Police to maintain security because of their limited capacity, but should also reinstall the cooperation of the Army. \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid acknowledged in his written \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  speech, delivered by Vice President Megawati Soekarnoputri, the pressing security problems at home and said that the government would strengthen the role of the Police as the "protector of the people and preventer of all (disorder) and security disturbances." \par \par \uc2  In a related development, the International Monetary Fund called the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  a "sensible" \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan which was trying to cope with the sensitive issues of \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization. \par \par \uc2  "It does move toward cutting \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and deals with decentralization in a balanced way," IMF senior resident representative in Jakarta John Dodsworth told Reuters. \par \par \uc2  "The difficulty will come in the implementation of decentralization, to make sure what's written in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is implemented in practice," Dodsworth added. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft allocates more than Rp 74 trillion or around a quarter of the total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to provincial and district administrations to help them carry out their new political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  roles. \par \par \uc2  The autonomy and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  decentralization \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is seen as a crucial measure to help prevent the country from tearing apart.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dwa3003yx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
