\par\par \b \uc2  JSX loses appeal as capitalization of local mart falls. \b0\par\par\uc2 595 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 October 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The sharp decline in the capitalization of the local stock market resulting from the impact of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis has caused it to lose its appeal to global equity investors, according to a senior executive of a foreign investment management firm. \par \par \uc2  The chairman of the New-York based investment firm Tocqueville Asset Management L.P., Franscois Sicart on Monday cited the decline of the JSX's market capitalization as discouraging foreign equity investors, on top of prevailing political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "In the case of Indonesia, it (foreign equity investment) has a small impact; much lower than foreign direct investment," Sicart said. \par \par \uc2  He said that although the JSX's market value stood at $23 billion, less than $10 billion was available to the investing \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  because the rest was still controlled by founders of the companies and the government. \par \par \uc2  "For a U.S. or British pension fund this is small change," he said, adding that large investment firms manage funds totaling hundreds of billions of U.S. dollars. \par \par \uc2  Even though the JSX's market capitalization grew significantly from Rp 215 trillion in 1996 to Rp 367 trillion as of March this year, in terms of dollars it had dropped significantly to $41 billion from $89 billion due to the steep fall in the rupiah value against the American greenback. \par \par \uc2  Furthermore, foreign equity investment in 1996 was sustained by a stable political environment. \par \par \uc2  In order to help the market regain its appeal, the government must relinquish more stakes in publicly listed state companies, he said, adding that the increase in the supply of the stocks to the investing \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  would encourage investors to return to the market. \par \par \uc2  But he said he understood the government delaying its divestment plans due to unfavorable market condition. \par \par \uc2  The government recently delayed divesting its stakes in publicly listed PT Bank Central Asia and PT Bank Niaga, after the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  argued that market sentiment was unfavorable. \par \par \uc2  "Any delay will have an impact on confidence, on the other hand, business people are more practical, realizing that not everything can be done overnight," he said. \par \par \uc2  According to him, Indonesia should not rely too much on foreigners to revive its capital market because they, mostly short-term oriented investors in nature, were so unpredictable. Their presence is often unhealthy and it often causes volatile market movements. \par \par \uc2  "At the moment, you don't really want stock investors to come back," Sicart said. \par \par \uc2  He advised the Indonesian government should instead try to improve the investment climate to attract foreign direct investment. \par \par \uc2  According to him, foreign direct investors required some encouragement from the legal side, such as the sanctuarity of contracts or the reliability of the court. \par \par \uc2  "Under the old regime, there was some predictability about the way things were done, now you have democracy and an unreliable juridical system which frightens people," he explained. \par \par \uc2  He said that foreign investors highest concern was seeing stability return to Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Sicart's Tocqueville manages a total of $1.5 billion in funds, of which 80 percent is invested in the U.S. market. \par \par \uc2  The firms' clients have an average of five year investment interest in several blue chips companies at JSX, such as PT Unilever Indonesia, telecommunication firms PT Telekomunikasi Indonesia and PT Indosat as well as mining company PT International Nickel Indonesia (INCO). \par \par \uc2  "I look more at the macro \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , because what will unlock the value (of these companies) is the improvement in the political and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  macro picture," he said. (bkm) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dwaa001pj\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  'BLBI conflict affects  \highlight22\uc2 central bank \highlight\uc2  performance'. \b0\par\par\uc2 425 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 October 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The BLBI case is considered to have affected \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank \b0 \highlight\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2  Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's performance in its function maintaining monetary stability and \par \par \uc2  has led the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  vulnerable in facing new sudden crisis. \par \par \uc2  Boediono, former \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  director said there are at least three \par \par \uc2  reasons why the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Liquidity Support (BLBI) case needs to be \par \par \uc2  settled immediately. First, the BLBI status has an immediate affect on \par \par \uc2  BI's balance sheet. This would eventually limit BI's space to move and its \par \par \uc2  performance to maintain monetary stability. \par \par \uc2  He made the remarks yesterday in a seminar, which also presented BI Deputy \par \par \uc2  Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah and former IMF Asia Pacific Director Hubert \par \par \uc2  Neiss as speakers. Economist Sri Mulyani was moderator. \par \par \uc2  According to Boediono, if the BLBI case is left unsolved, BI will never be \par \par \uc2  ready facing a new crisis that come suddenly. Second, the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \par \par \uc2  the BLBI case is because no agreements have been reached on the \par \par \uc2  regulations and institutional relationship between BI and the government. \par \par \uc2  True that government ruling No. 23/1999 on BI has already outlined he \par \par \uc2  relationship between BI and the government, but they are still too general \par \par \uc2  and implicit, he said. \par \par \uc2  BI's function as the lender of the last resort, for example, has not been \par \par \uc2  outlined explicitly. There is no explanation on who will carry the burden \par \par \uc2  if the function as the lender of the last resort is implemented. \par \par \uc2  Third, the human resources at BI could not work in their maximum capacity \par \par \uc2  due to the BLBI \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Not ready \par \par \uc2  According to Boediono, BI could not lend its optimum support on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  recovery because of the three problems above and it is not ready to face \par \par \uc2  any new possible crisis. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile Sri Mulyani said aside from the legal enforcement, BI should \par \par \uc2  continue to claim the BLBI funds to the debtors and at the same time \par \par \uc2  maintain its roles. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Deputy Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah said the BLBI case \par \par \uc2  settlement should be focused on getting back the BLBI fund. But the \par \par \uc2  country has a potential loss of Rp138 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile former IMF Asia Pacific Director Hubert Neiss said he disagrees \par \par \uc2  if IBRA sells the assets in a hurry and only generate low revenue, but he \par \par \uc2  also reminded if the government cannot wait too long because the \par \par \uc2  government needs the fund desperately. \par \par \uc2  Neiss added the government should not continue to wait because the value \par \par \uc2  of the assets could depreciate. That's why the government has to make sure \par \par \uc2  IBRA set the schedule on when to sell the assets. (m12/yn/msw). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dwab000kz\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  JSX bearish, BI-40 down 0.88%. \b0\par\par\uc2 314 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 October 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA: The bearish trading situation at the JSX plus the lack of \par \par \uc2  positive market sentiments has triggered the investors to sell some of \par \par \uc2  their big cap shares. \par \par \uc2  The JSX composite index closed lower 0.59% or 2.449 points to 412.915. The \par \par \uc2  total volume of shares traded in the regular market was 332.674 million \par \par \uc2  units worth Rp184.095 billion, despite foreign net selling of Rp33.798 \par \par \uc2  billion. \par \par \uc2  The selling pressure in the bourse yesterday also dragged the LQ-45 lower \par \par \uc2  by 0.587 points (0.74%) to close at 78.379. The index 40 Bisnis (BI-40) \par \par \uc2  fell 0.88% or 0.799 points to 90.020. \par \par \uc2  Investors seemed reluctant to take buying positions amid the unfavorable \par \par \uc2  bourse condition, especially since the political, security and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  conditions are still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the RI-IMF rift, Hubert Neiss' warning of \par \par \uc2  a second recapitalization has contributed to the negative sentiments in \par \par \uc2  the bourse. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the weak regional and global bourses in the last few days have \par \par \uc2  also discouraged the investors to speculate on shares. Investors are still \par \par \uc2  adopting a wait and see stance and waiting for good news from senior \par \par \uc2  economics minister Rizal Ramli who is now in Tokyo to attend the CGI \par \par \uc2  meeting and investors are also waiting for the UN security council to meet \par \par \uc2  on 13 October to discuss the progress report on how the Indonesian \par \par \uc2  government handled the Atambua case. \par \par \uc2  On the other hand Parliament Speaker Amien Rais has warned President Gus \par \par \uc2  Dur not to challenge the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  to hold a special meeting and \par \par \uc2  reminded Gus Dur would go down if he continues to challenge the parliament \par \par \uc2  and create investors' fears. \par \par \uc2  These are the reasons why foreign securities like Merrill Lynch and Jardin \par \par \uc2  Flemings continued their selling pressures on the blue chips. In \par \par \uc2  yesterday's trading, 17 of Bisnis shares suffered losses. \par \par \uc2  * Sigma Research Institute. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dwab000l2\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
