\par\par \b \uc2  PROSPECTS FOR RI'S  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  RECOVERY STILL  \highlight22\uc2 UNCERTAIN \highlight\uc2 , SAYS WB OFFICIAL. \b0\par\par\uc2 327 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 October 2000\par \uc2 ANTARA - The Indonesian National News Agency\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Asia Pulse Pte Limited. Asia Pulse gives no warranty or guarantee as to the accuracy of the information, Asia Pulse shall not be liable for errors or omissions in, or delays or interruptions to or cessation of delivery of, the data through its negligence or otherwise.\par \par \uc2  Jakarta, Oct 13 (ANTARA) - The current favourable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation in Indonesia has yet to guarantee recovery, World Bank Vice President for East Asia and the Pacific Jemal-ud-din Kassum said here Friday. \par \par \uc2  Various problems relating to the country's unity, its cabinet and the role of its military in political and social affairs had drained the nation's energy and there was little energy left to seriously discuss a strategy and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for development, Kassum said. \par \par \uc2  Kassum said  the progress Indonesia had made in its efforts to achieve \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery could only be called modest. \par \par \uc2  With only little time left, Kassum added, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery \par \par \uc2  efforts could easily be thrown off the track by a nervous market, outflow of \par \par \uc2  investors and fragile confidence. \par \par \uc2  Despite some positive indicators such as a declining  inflation rate, \par \par \uc2  increased wages, less poverty, increased  exports and earnings from oil, various \par \par \uc2  non-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems could make those indicators meaningless. \par \par \uc2  "The money market remains unconvinced about the real developments in the \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Political instability, unrest in many regions and violence continue to depress the rupiah and the stock market, while \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are increasing and foreign investors are fleeing the country," Kassum said. \par \par \uc2  Market \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  could also be sparked by wrong \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The new government had been quick in drawing up a comprehensive reform program but was not equally good in implementating those programs. \par \par \uc2  As a result, Kassum said, although most of Indonesia's macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies were already on the right track, their implementation was often subject to long delays. \par \par \uc2  In addition, failures in trade policies such as in the setting of rice and sugar prices and the creation of new barriers to foreign investment had given rise to doubts about Indonesia's commitment to free trade. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, it should not be surprising if we say that the prospects for Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery are still far from safe," Kassum said. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dwad000sl\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  CGI commitment about US$4,5 billion. \b0\par\par\uc2 599 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 October 2000\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The World Bank has said that without corporate debt restructuring, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery would lose steam. \par \par \uc2  It is also estimated that CGI loans to Indonesia would be in the US$4,5 billion-US$5 billion range, said World Bank senior official Jemal-ud-din Kassum here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  He added that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery is proceeding - with growth projected at 4% this year-but that no less important is its sustainability. \par \par \uc2  "To attain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth sustainability, corporate debt restructuring is very important in order to obtain fresh funds, new investment and to recover activities of the banking system," he said in a press conference on the eve of the Consultative Group for Indonesia (CGI) meeting in Tokyo, 17-18 October. \par \par \uc2  Kassum added "accelerating restructuring is imperative, as without new credits and investments as the locomotive of recovery, it would lose steam." \par \par \uc2  Kassum also said that the CGI forum would come under world attention and also the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The meting would also discuss corruption, illegal logging, good governance and decentralization besides the Atambua case. \par \par \uc2  "We are happy with the government's explanation on Atambua, but a number of donors have strongly linked Atambua with aid," he said. \par \par \uc2  In the CGI meeting next week, he said, Indonesia needs aid for loans and programs worth US$4,9 billion (with the new \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 2001 assuming the US$ at Rp7,300). \par \par \uc2  "We can not as yet mention the exact figure as the meeting takes place next week." \par \par \uc2  The World Bank in its report prior to the CGI meeting said the need for loans to plug the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the next \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 2001 is about US$4,5-US$5 billion. \par \par \uc2  Kassum said donors wish to see progress in the settlement of the Atambua case. \par \par \uc2  "Progress in this respect is very important to ascertain donor support," he said. \par \par \uc2  Slow progress in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  are factors that influence investor confidence in Indonesia despite clear signals that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was recovering, he said. \par \par \uc2  "However, we must be realistic about the condition of the market. The money market remains unsatisfactory over the situation," he said. \par \par \uc2  On decentralization, World Bank economist Vikram Nehru pointed at the risk of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  imbalance between the central government and regional governments. \par \par \uc2  Regions that are allowed to seek foreign loans from donors and markets need to set up a new mechanism as the World Bank and the ADB could not provide loans directly to them but must go through the central government. \par \par \uc2  The Bank notes that Indonesia faces "trying times." \par \par \uc2  The ten-point program of senior economics minister Rizal Ramli, said the Bank, is "quite promising". \par \par \uc2  Rizal, who yesterday met with House members, reasserted that Indonesia has yet to decide on whether to seek debt relief. \par \par \uc2  Rizal said several House members have suggested that principal loans be scrapped. But many argued that Indonesia is not in a position to seek such a facility, as the country is not a poor country. \par \par \uc2  However, there are also those who say that it would not be fair to burden the next generations as there were corruption and collusion (KKN) in the past, including on foreign aid. \par \par \uc2  "The government has yet to take a position on whether we should seek relief on principal debt or not," he said. \par \par \uc2  Rizal added that as an alternative the government would seek loans from the International Development Assistance (IDA) at a rate of 0% for the next 30 years. \par \par \uc2  "The soft loan could help Indonesia finance projects that would allow it to come out of the crisis." (dj/ens/ab). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010804dwae000m0\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picw