 a year, not to mention the massive burden of the equivalent of US$73 billion in government domestic debts incurred just over the past 12 months. Moreover, the US$4.8 billion pledged on Wednesday was not entirely fresh loans. \par \par \uc2  Most importantly, the government should pay serious attention to the warning \par \par \uc2  shots given by major creditors at the Tokyo meeting. \par \par \uc2  The creditors expressed disappointment with the sluggishness of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  reforms, especially the pace and quality of corporate restructuring. They voiced great concern over political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , regional unrest, periodical outbursts of violence and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  slippage on the structural reform agenda. \par \par \uc2  Failure to take appropriate action could weaken the market sentiment and slow or even subvert recovery. - The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2  ENDLESS DEBT \par \par \uc2  The Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) on Wednesday agreed to provide US$ \par \par \uc2  4.8 billion in new loans to the country to fill part of its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 2001 beginning January. \par \par \uc2  This despite doubts that human rights issues, such as the one in East Timor, \par \par \uc2  would prompt donors not to extend new loans. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian delegation in the CGI meeting in Tokyo should thus not feel \par \par \uc2  happy with their success in convincing the donor countries. \par \par \uc2  The country's total debts have reached US$ 143.3 billion.  The huge loans \par \par \uc2  must be repaid surely by the next generations. \par \par \uc2  The money should thus be used only for the people's sake and with great \par \par \uc2  responsibility. \par \par \uc2  We should learn from the past that corrupt, collusive and nepotistic \par \par \uc2  practices (KKN) damages the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector. \par \par \uc2  If the debts are used with full responsibility, Indonesia will not beg for \par \par \uc2  debts every year. -- Bisnis Indonesia \par \par \uc2  SUWONDO'S MYSTERY \par \par \uc2  Knowing that Suwondo has finally been arrested, the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  must feel \par \par \uc2  relieved because this is about a big case -- one which puts at stake the \par \par \uc2  position and honor of President Abdurrahman Wahid. \par \par \uc2  We hope that Suwondo would speak of facts in court, including whether or not \par \par \uc2  President Abdurrahman Wahid was involved in the Rp 35 billion Bulog scandal. \par \par \uc2  However, a new mystery has emerged.  Police have arrested Suwondo but could \par \par \uc2  not interrogate him due to his ill health. \par \par \uc2  This means that the first duty of the police in the Rp 35 billion scam is to \par \par \uc2  take Suwondo to a doctor. \par \par \uc2  It is thus not impossible if the "trial by doctors" part 2 follows the trial \par \par \uc2  of former president, Soeharto. \par \par \uc2  Suwondo has only kept silent.  What will happen if he remains silent?  Is he \par \par \uc2  silent because he is suffering from mental illness?  Can we bring persons with \par \par \uc2  mental illness to court? \par \par \uc2  A scandal is a scandal.  Suwondo is a mystery by himself.  He has been \par \par \uc2  arrested.  But what's the use of arresting a person who is likely to be declared \par \par \uc2  suffering from mental illness? \par \par \uc2  Let us just wait and see whether it was an achievement to arrest Suwondo, or \par \par \uc2  it was just "planned coincidence". - Media Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document antara0020010804dwaj000uq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
