\par\par \b \uc2  CGI loan provides certainty to state  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 698 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 October 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The US$4.8 billion loan pledged on Wednesday by Indonesia's traditional donors would have a positive impact on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as it provides certainty to next year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , experts said. \par \par \uc2  Economist Pande Raja Silalahi said the loan would help plug next year's huge state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimated at around $6 billion or 3.7 percent of the gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  "It is positive for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because it provides certainty to the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said Pande Raja Silalahi, an economist at the leading private think tank, Center for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS). \par \par \uc2  Donors grouped in the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) pledged $4.8 billion in aid for 2001 and planned to provide another $530 million in technical assistance grants, at the end of their two-day meeting in Tokyo. \par \par \uc2  But Pande said that it was still unclear whether the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  would agree for the government to take such a huge foreign loan, particularly amid strong oil prices. \par \par \uc2  He said that the House might ask the government to take a smaller foreign loan. \par \par \uc2  "The country's foreign loans are already huge and they have now become a big problem," he said. \par \par \uc2  The government unveiled the draft of the 2001 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  with an estimated \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of around Rp 53 trillion or $7.2 billion based on an exchange rate of Rp 7,300. \par \par \uc2  The government has said the bulk of the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be financed by foreign loans, while the remainder would be financed by the sale of assets held by the Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) and the privatization program. \par \par \uc2  The government assumed an international oil price of $22 per barrel in the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . But analysts and legislators have said the assumption was too conservative given that the international oil price had been hovering at more than $29 per barrel. \par \par \uc2  The House and the government are still debating the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft and are expected to reach a final agreement sometime in November. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the CGI's new loan commitment had little impact on the rupiah or the local stock market. \par \par \uc2  The announcement of the CGI loan commitment helped lift the rupiah from an intraday low of Rp 8,950 to end the day at Rp 8,895 but it was still lower than the Rp 8,845 in late trading on Tuesday. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said the rupiah remained under pressure due to fears over \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the domestic political development, particularly after the House unveiled its plan to probe into President Abdurrahman Wahid's possible role in the financial scandals. \par \par \uc2  After climbing for two consecutive days, the Jakarta Stock Exchange composite index ended 0.1 percent lower at 416.948 points. \par \par \uc2  Separately, former finance minister Bambang Sudibyo welcomed the success of Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rizal Ramli and his team in obtaining the CGI loan but questioned the conditions for the loan. \par \par \uc2  Bambang said if the conditions were too heavy, the loan would only cause problems for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said that although CGI had always agreed to provide loans to Indonesia during the past several years, the conditions had gradually become heavier. \par \par \uc2  "Before the (1997) \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, the interest rate of the loan was between 1 percent and 3 percent but now there are donor countries who are demanding a 5 percent interest rate which is equal to a commercial loan," he said. \par \par \uc2  Bambang said that as an alternative to this loan, the government could push its privatization efforts and the sale of the IBRA assets. \par \par \uc2  Most analysts said that with the approval of the new loan, the government must push its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  restructuring program, particularly the sale of assets under IBRA. \par \par \uc2  The government recently delayed a key divestment program involving the publicly listed Bank Central Asia (BCA) and Bank Niaga. \par \par \uc2  The delay had disappointed both the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund which are providing a separate multibillion dollar bailout for the country. \par \par \uc2  IBRA controls assets worth more than Rp 600 trillion. The assets had been transferred to the agency from the country's troubled banks and ex-bank owners. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2000 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010812dwaj001e1\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
