\par\par \b \uc2  KL investor eyes Rp 6 trillion toll road project. \b0\par\par\uc2 553 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 November 2000\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2000 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Malaysia's DRB-Hi Com is considering financing the long delayed construction of the Rp 6 trillion (about US$674 million) worth Jakarta Outer Ring Road (JORR) project, state-owned toll road company PT Jasa Marga said on Thursday. \par \par \uc2  Jasa Marga president Wiyoga Adiwasito said the Malaysian company had signed a memorandum of understanding early this year and he hoped the work on the toll road project would resume next year. \par \par \uc2  "The entrance of the investor is expected to accelerate the completion of the project," Wiyoga said in a written response during a hearing with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' Commission IV for infrastructure and transportation affairs. \par \par \uc2  He said Jasa Marga revoked the 35-year concession rights of JORR's former three operators after they defaulted on their debts. \par \par \uc2  JORR's initial operators were PT Citra Mataram Satriamarga Persada, PT Marga Nurindo Bhakti and PT Citra Bhakti Margatama Persada. They obtained the contract from Jasa Marga to operate the toll road under a Build-Operate-Transfer (BOT) scheme long before the crisis hit the country in late 1997. \par \par \uc2  The three investors financed the project with loans worth Rp 1 trillion from local banks. The loans turned sour after the government suspended JORR's development in 1998. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) took over the nonperforming loans extended to the three companies from the nationalized banks. \par \par \uc2  Wiyoga said IBRA and Jasa Marga then formed a joint venture, called New Co, to continue the project. \par \par \uc2  Jasa Marga's director of operation Marjanto said New Co was founded to accommodate the assets that belonged to IBRA and Jasa Marga. \par \par \uc2  Jasa Marga and IBRA will convert their loans into equity in the new company, although the composition of ownership are still being negotiated, he said. \par \par \uc2  New Co, he went on, would then operate the project but must first seek investors. \par \par \uc2  However, Marjanto warned that it was not easy to find investors interested enough to enter the toll road industry. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tariff\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2  He said a major constraint in attracting investors to finance toll road projects was the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates. \par \par \uc2  "When can we raise \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates, on what basis can we raise them? These require \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , otherwise how can investors calculate their income?," he said. \par \par \uc2  Under the current government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No 8/1990, the president approves a \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  hike under the recommendation of the minister of transportation. \par \par \uc2  Marjanto said the last the government raised toll \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates was nine years ago. \par \par \uc2  "Considering the inflation rate, we expect a hike of about 30 percent," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said because of this \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Malaysian investor was still hesitant to join the JORR project. \par \par \uc2  Jasa Marga and the government, he continued, were working on clarifying the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  hikes. \par \par \uc2  "We then hope construction will start sometime in mid-2001," he added. \par \par \uc2  Wiyoga said under an improved investment climate next year, the company planned to resume several toll roa